        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I guess even that would be possible with the same one-line change in `get_statuscol_str()` but that would place the burden on the 'statuscolumn' plugin/user.\r\n\r\nIn theory you could only repeat certain signs on wrapped lines by evaluating the sign column in your 'statuscolumn' but that seems like the wrong way to go about it.\r\n\r\nI think in this case it would make more sense to add a `wrap/repeat` option to `sign_place()`, resolving this feature request for both a default and 'statuscolumn' gutter at the same time (since 'statuscolumn' simply copies the default sign column).",
