        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "(In the mean time?) it is possible to do this on a per-sign basis when implementing custom sign segments for `'statuscolumn'` through `sign_getplaced()`/`nvim_buf_get_extmarks()`. I recently added support for this in my statuscolumn plugin and just added an option to enable wrapping per sign segment as well. Note the left sign segment with diagnostic signs that are not repeated and the right segment after the line number with git signs that are repeated:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31730729/233513492-019ad7fb-76f9-4e92-acd6-d69fc06f9e76.png)\r\n",
